I do think that this is subtly broken, and has been since we started handling recursive types. What we really want to say is that the following two types are equal:

```
struct {
    x int
    y self
}

struct {
    x int
    y self
}
```

Note that I'm deliberately avoiding the use of names here, as the type system doesn't give names to object types. I considered making that change, but it's quite a bit more disruptive. It might be worth doing, however, as it may reduce the equality problem to "just check the names".

