The methods are not named that well, but I copied the main differences from the header file:
```
SubscribeWaitDependencies
  /// The TaskDependencyManager will track all remote dependencies until the
  /// dependencies are local, or until UnsubscribeWaitDependencies is called
  /// with the same worker ID, whichever occurs first.
```
```
SubscribeGetDependencies
  /// The TaskDependencyManager will track the task's dependencies
  /// until UnsubscribeGetDependencies is called on the same task ID.
```

So SubscribeGetDependencies is supposed to be for tasks that are blocked on some dependencies, and SubscribeWaitDependencies is for a worker that is subscribing asynchronously to stream of dependencies (like with `ray.wait`). I think this class could use a refactor though :)

